it.ozimov.cirneco.hamcrest.java7

Class J7Matchers

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.ozimov.cirneco.hamcrest.java7.J7Matchers
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    J8Matchers

    public class J7Matchers
extends Object
    The J7Matchers class groups all the matchers introduced by Cirneco's Hamcrest extension for Java 7. Suggested use would be to import all the static methods of this class in a unit tes.
    Since:
    version 0.1 for JDK7

      • between

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> between(T from,
                                                                        T to)
        Creates a matcher for Ts that matches when the compareTo() method returns a value between from and to, both excluded.

        For example: 

        assertThat(10, between(10, 11))
        will return false.

      • betweenInclusive

        Creates a matcher for Ts that matches when the compareTo() method returns a value between from and to, both included.

        For example: 

        assertThat(10, betweenInclusive(10, 11))
        will return true.

      • betweenLowerBoundInclusive

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> betweenLowerBoundInclusive(T from,
                                                                                           T to)
        Creates a matcher for Ts that matches when the compareTo() method returns a value between from and to, both included.

        For example: 

        assertThat(10, betweenLowerBoundInclusive(10, 11))
        will return true. while: 
        assertThat(11, betweenLowerBoundInclusive(10, 11))
        will return false.

      • after

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> after(T value)
        Creates a matcher of a Comparable object that matches when the examined object is after the given value, as reported by the compareTo method of the examined object.

        E.g.: Date past; Date now; assertThat(now, after(past));

        The matcher renames the Hamcrest matcher obtained with Matchers.greaterThan(Comparable).

      • afterOrEqual

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> afterOrEqual(T value)
        Creates a matcher of Comparable object that matches when the examined object is after or equal with respect to object value, as reported by the compareTo method of the examined object.

        E.g.: Date past; Date now; assertThat(now, afterOrEqual(now)); assertThat(now, afterOrEqual(past));

        The matcher renames the Hamcrest matcher obtained with Matchers.greaterThanOrEqualTo(Comparable).

      • before

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> before(T value)
        Creates a matcher of Comparable object that matches when the examined object is before the given value, as reported by the compareTo method of the examined object.

        E.g.: Date past; Date now; assertThat(past, before(now));

        The matcher renames the Hamcrest matcher obtained with Matchers.lessThan(Comparable).

      • beforeOrEqual

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> beforeOrEqual(T value)
        Creates a matcher of Comparable object that matches when the examined object is before or equal with respect to object value, as reported by the compareTo method of the examined object.

        E.g.: Date past; Date now; assertThat(now, beforeOrEqual(now)); assertThat(past, beforeOrEqual(now));

        The matcher renames the Hamcrest matcher obtained with Matchers.lessThanOrEqualTo(Comparable).

      • hasToStringContainingInOrder

        public static <T> org.hamcrest.Matcher<T> hasToStringContainingInOrder(Object... items)
        Creates a matcher that matches any examined object whose toString method returns a value that contains all the substrings given by the toString() method called on the given list of items, considering the order of their appearance. For example: 
        assertThat("AClass{a_field=a value, another_field=another value}",
  ContainingInOrder("a value","another value"))

      • containsInAnyOrder

        public static <T> org.hamcrest.Matcher<Iterable<? extends T>> containsInAnyOrder(Iterable<T> items)

        Creates an order agnostic matcher for Iterables that matches when a single pass over the examined Iterable yields a series of items, each logically equal to one item anywhere in the specified items. For a positive match, the examined iterable must be of the same length as the number of specified items.

        N.B. each of the specified items will only be used once during a given examination, so be careful when specifying items that may be equal to more than one entry in an examined iterable. For example:


         //Arrange
 Iterable actual = Arrays.asList("foo", "bar");
 Iterable expected = Arrays.asList("bar", "foo");

 //Assert
 assertThat(actual, containsInAnyOrder(expected));
        Parameters:
        items - the items that must equal the items provided by an examined Iterable in any order

      • containsInOrder

        public static <T> org.hamcrest.Matcher<Iterable<? extends T>> containsInOrder(Iterable<T> items)
        Creates a matcher for Iterables that matches when a single pass over the examined Iterable yields a series of items, each logically equal to the corresponding item in the specified items. For a positive match, the examined iterable must be of the same length as the number of specified items.

 //Assert

        Parameters:
        items - the items that must equal the items provided by an examined Iterable

      • containsInRelativeOrder

        public static <T> org.hamcrest.Matcher<Iterable<? extends T>> containsInRelativeOrder(Iterable<T> items)
        Creates a matcher for Iterables that matches when a single pass over the examined Iterable yields a series of items, that contains items logically equal to the corresponding item in the specified items, in the same relative order For example:

        For example: 

         //Arrange

 //Assert

        Parameters:
        items - the items that must be contained within items provided by an examined Iterable in the same relative order

      • containedIn

        public static <K> org.hamcrest.Matcher<Iterable<K>> containedIn(Iterable<? super K> comparison)
        Creates a matcher for Iterables matching when the examined Iterable has all the elements in the comparison Iterable, without repetitions. For instance: List<String> comparison = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "foo"); List<String> given = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "bar"); assertThat(given, is(containedIn(comparison)); returns false because element bar in given is not counted 3 times in comparison. While: List<String> comparison = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "bar", "foo"); List<String> given = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "bar"); assertThat(given, is(containedIn(comparison)); returns true because all the elements in given are found in comparison with the same frequency.

For instance: List<String> comparison = Arrays.asList("bar", "foo"); List<String> given = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar"); assertThat(given, sameSizeOf(comparison)); returns true while List<String> comparison = Arrays.asList("bar", "foo"); List<String> given = Arrays.asList("bar"); assertThat(given, sameSizeOf(comparison)); returns false.

      • subsetOf

        public static <K> org.hamcrest.Matcher<Iterable<K>> subsetOf(Iterable<? super K> comparison)
        Creates a matcher for Iterables matching when the examined Iterable has all the elements in the comparison Iterable, without repetitions (i.e. it is a subset). For instance: List<String> comparison = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "foo"); List<String> given = Arrays.asList("bar", "bar", "bar"); assertThat(given, is(subsetOf(comparison)); returns true because each element of given is included in comparison. Essentially, if the set view of the given iterables guarantee that given is a subset of comparison, then the matcher returns true

      • infinity

        public static <N extends Number> org.hamcrest.Matcher<N> infinity()

        will return false. while:
